==English==

===Etymology===
A corruption of Then Ones. The(n-ones).  "The miller was a stout one for the nones" - Chaucer. Later c substituted for s.  "A chalice for the nonce" - Shakespeare.

===Noun===
'''nonce'''
{{wikipedia}}

# The one or single occasion; the present call or purpose; -- chiefly used in ''[[for the nonce]]''.
#: ''That will do for the nonce, but we'll need a better answer for the long term.''
# {{lex}} A [[nonce word]].
#: ''I had thought that the term was a nonce, but it seems like it's been picked up by other authors.''
# (''cryptography'') A datum constructed so as to be unique to a particular message in a stream, in order to prevent [[replay attack]]s.
#: ''In this protocol we use the serial number of the message as a nonce.''
# (''British, vulgar'') A [[pedophile]].

